<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-12">
        <h4>0. Open ssh terminal in VM</h4>
            <pre>vagrant ssh</pre>
        <h4>1. Chek Open Flow Controller Rest Server status</h4>
      {{#if serverOnline}}
          <div class="alert alert-success">
              Open Flow controller REST server is online. Please go to the next step.
          </div>
      {{else}}
          <div class="alert alert-danger">
              Open Flow controller REST server is offline, please launch it with the following command inside VM.
          </div>
          <pre>ryu-manager ./vendor/ryu/ryu/app/ofctl_rest.py</pre>
      {{/if}}
        <h4>2. Launch Mininet in VM</h4>
        Example:
        <pre>sudo mn --topo=tree,1,3 --mac --controller=remote --switch ovsk,protocols=OpenFlow13</pre>

        <h4>3. Check Stats menu point and click {{link-to 'Switches' 'stats.switches'}}</h4>
        <p>It lists all available switches.</p>

        <h4>4. Add new flow rules by clicking on {{link-to 'Add Flow' 'add-flow'}}</h4>
        <p>Use the given format for creating Match and Actions.</p>

        <h4>5. Check flows clicking on {{link-to 'Stats' 'stats'}} menu and {{link-to 'Flows' 'stats.flows'}} submenu.</h4>
        <p>It shows all switches and connected flows.</p>
    </div>
</div>